Congress did, of course, already pass roughly $2.5 trillion to jump-start the federal government’s response to the dual economic and public health crises.
But public hearings have been on pause for weeks, and there’s little House committee leaders can do if the White House resists its efforts.
House Rules Committee Chairman James McGovern.
